This weekend was so dope....Thank you once again to my partners @jpmorgan @chase .....I visited  Castlemont High School & Oakland High School & talked about financial literacy with some amazing kids...The conversation was real & honest. I opened up about my financial failures & also discussed the lack of information that we as a community receive when it comes to money & money management. I‚Äôm having these conversations because I want to see a change...this is a start. I also visited The Hive business district in Uptown Oakland and made stops in several minority owned businesses...The goal is to not only support these businesses but also make our youth aware of other entrepreneurs that are living proof that dreams can come true. They just have to be worked for....let‚Äôs continue to grind and do the work...the success will come. I want to personally acknowledge these businesses & their owners:
Sweet Bar Bakery- Eddie Viat
Dapper Dans barber loft- Danny.D
Taylor Jay- Taylor Jay
Firebrand Bakery- Matt Kreutz 
Calavera- Chris & Jana Pastena
McMullen- Sherri McMullen
Brown Sugar Kitchen-Tonya Holland

I‚Äôm proud to say that @jpmorgan @chase is making this issue a priority & is allowing me & @stephencurry30 to travel & personally talk to our kids of today & tomorrow....The change starts now and it starts with us taking responsibility to correct the things that need the most correcting!!!!! #HartofitAll #Chase #FinancialFitness #LiveLoveLaugh

The 1st was the "The Upside" which was an unbelievable story....Now I'm doing "Fatherhood" which is a movie based off of Matthew Logelin's life. What this man has been thru is unreal....he is the definition of Tru strength in my eyes...he lost his wife after she delivered their baby at the hospital. His life took a turn that he never saw coming....while facing his darkest moment in his life he was left with the responsibility of raising his child. Nobody believed in him or his ability to step up to the plate...but he did it. It was hard and grueling but he found a way to pour all of the love he had into his daughter "Madeline " because that's what his wife would have wanted him to do....Matt & Maddy came to visit us on set today...both of their smiles bought a different type of energy to our set. I'm in awe of their story and even more so of this opportunity. Their bond is inseparable and rightfully so.  I can't wait for the world to see what this man and his daughter made it thru.....#Fatherhood #ComingSoon #MeAndMelodyAeeDoingOurBestToMakeYouProud ....Trust me when I tell you that this is a movie that we all need to see.
